And I wanted to suggest for this group to consider that assistant principals will not be designated as the investigator for bullying reports that occur as the result of participation in an athletics or extracurricular program, because the reporting structure is such that those assistant principals

192
00:24:01,161 --> 00:24:07,963
don't really have any authority over the athletics director or programming, right?

193
00:24:08,003 --> 00:24:09,644
That typically sits at a higher level.

194
00:24:09,764 --> 00:24:14,425
So I wanted to offer that to this group for some thoughts.

195
00:24:14,465 --> 00:24:19,787
I mean, I think that particularly is relevant at the high school, I think to some degree at the middle school.

196
00:24:21,407 --> 00:24:25,769
But I know that we have had a number of bullying related

197
00:24:27,963 --> 00:24:30,944
reports surrounding athletics.

198
00:24:31,124 --> 00:24:42,566
So I wanted there to be, at least for me, I wanted there to be a clear distinction around how we handle reports of athletics bullying so that they are investigated thoroughly.

199
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:44,126
So I don't know what you all think about that.

200
00:24:45,387 --> 00:24:48,827
Well, I like it.

201
00:24:49,527 --> 00:24:51,768
I think that if we do change the structure

202
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:56,367
of the organization, then some of these things would probably have to be looked at again.

203
00:24:56,627 --> 00:24:59,087
But in the current structure, I think it makes sense.

204
00:25:00,588 --> 00:25:09,550
And I don't know on the ground what that looks like and if there will be challenges around.

205
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:17,332
Well, this is about the investigation, so who's going to be the person that takes the report wouldn't necessarily be different, but

206
00:25:19,074 --> 00:25:27,838
You know, we wouldn't want to have a middle school person, a student trying to report something and have to go to the high school.

207
00:25:27,858 --> 00:25:30,359
That would be terrible.

208
00:25:30,679 --> 00:25:41,004
But, and you do say investigator, so it's not that the person who is going to be responsible for receiving the reports would be any different, right?

209
00:25:41,745 --> 00:25:42,205
Correct.

210
00:25:43,165 --> 00:25:45,686
And actually this might belong somewhere else, but,

211
00:25:47,475 --> 00:25:49,958
I will make a note of that and we can circle back to that at the end.

212
00:25:51,279 --> 00:25:59,068
Mr. It just feel like I can offer some perspective on that as a former assistant principal high school level to as well.

213
00:25:59,909 --> 00:26:08,338
Maybe perhaps to consider some sort of language where you know, maybe an assistant principal and athletic director would operate in tandem in during the investigation stages.

214
00:26:09,213 --> 00:26:17,759
Part of the reason why I actually like an assistant principal being involved is because they might be considered a trusted adult to be able to be a person to take a report like that.

215
00:26:17,779 --> 00:26:26,904
Plus they have a perspective of how that might or actions may be taken off the field or on the field in the athletic arena might impact the school environment too as well.

216
00:26:27,905 --> 00:26:31,467
And they are kind of the boots on the ground and might be able to set up an action plan.

217
00:26:31,988 --> 00:26:36,771
So as to, you know, kind of prevent any further type of retaliation or incidents to take place.

218
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:46,555
So maybe just the consideration of, um, having people operate in tandem, because I understand the dynamic that's being pointed out about how our assistant principals don't have oversight over athletic coaches.

219
00:26:47,035 --> 00:26:49,176
That's more of the athletic director and the current structure we have.

220
00:26:49,756 --> 00:26:54,218
But I think, um, you know, operating in tandem in a situation like this may be something worthy of consideration.

221
00:26:56,059 --> 00:26:56,519
Thank you.

222
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:58,620
That's really excellent point.

223
00:26:59,661 --> 00:27:00,541
Anybody else on this one?

224
00:27:00,561 --> 00:27:06,944
I don't know why I suddenly decided to try to drive a little bit, but it's clearly running.

225
00:27:07,797 --> 00:27:09,658
That's OK, I would.

226
00:27:10,539 --> 00:27:11,440
I would agree with Nick.

227
00:27:11,580 --> 00:27:14,542
I think it is important as a previous athletic director.

228
00:27:15,042 --> 00:27:23,608
You definitely want your AP doing the investigations right along with your athletic director and sometimes athletic directors don't always have.

229
00:27:24,709 --> 00:27:29,592
The clearance to investigate, so it depends on the district in the role.

230
00:27:31,273 --> 00:27:36,477
But I would highly suggest having the AP in tandem with the the athletic director on that.

231
00:27:38,508 --> 00:27:43,297
And I guess, you know, as I was thinking about this, I think these are all really good points.

232
00:27:43,517 --> 00:27:45,902
What I was thinking about was that

233
00:27:47,692 --> 00:28:02,836
these situations might rise to the level of being appropriate to say the principal will be the investigator rather than the... So that's sort of where my head was at was like, is this assistant principal work or is it principal work?

234
00:28:02,856 --> 00:28:05,696
So I don't know if you guys have thoughts about that.

235
00:28:06,056 --> 00:28:07,857
I think it depends on how big it is.

236
00:28:07,937 --> 00:28:12,478
I mean, you might have to interview 20 kids.

237
00:28:12,558 --> 00:28:16,899
In that case, I mean, you're gonna have a team and your principal will probably be part of that team.

238
00:28:18,035 --> 00:28:19,115
So, yeah.

239
00:28:20,956 --> 00:28:28,559
And my thought would be, you know, having the language of principal or designee, you know, maybe be fitting for the language we're looking for.

240
00:28:30,379 --> 00:28:30,539
Okay.

241
00:28:33,940 --> 00:28:35,981
I do, I could only jump on for 30 minutes.

242
00:28:36,001 --> 00:28:38,482
I have another obligation at five o'clock.

243
00:28:39,722 --> 00:28:41,603
If that ends early, I'll jump back on.

244
00:28:43,048 --> 00:28:44,628
So thank you.

245
00:28:44,829 --> 00:28:48,149
I'm sorry, I have to jump off, but if I can, I will jump right back on.

246
00:28:49,110 --> 00:28:49,570
Thanks.

247
00:28:50,050 --> 00:28:50,590
Thank you.

248
00:28:52,611 --> 00:28:59,633
But this next bullet I think is really, these next two bullets are really important.

249
00:28:59,753 --> 00:29:05,935
So one of the things that I think we've danced around a little bit as we have talked about this policy is

250
00:29:09,407 --> 00:29:19,635
I'll say confusion on the part of parents about like, what do they have to do to start a bullying investigation?

251
00:29:19,655 --> 00:29:30,803
And I think we've heard from lots of parents who say like, I've been reporting these things and then suddenly I get a form and this has been going on for months, right?

252
00:29:30,843 --> 00:29:32,905
And so why did I never get this form before now?

253
00:29:33,405 --> 00:29:35,127
And to me, as I thought about that,

254
00:29:35,867 --> 00:29:43,609
What I think is happening is there's not clarity around what constitutes a bullying report.

255
00:29:44,149 --> 00:29:45,050
Is it a form?

256
00:29:45,710 --> 00:29:47,330
Is it some amount of information?

257
00:29:47,510 --> 00:29:50,471
What is it that officially starts the clock?

258
00:29:50,551 --> 00:29:56,173
And I wanted this policy to be really, really clear about what starts that process.

259
00:29:58,199 --> 00:30:13,946
So I'm totally open to like what this sub bullet list is, but what this bullet says is Medford Public Schools will consider an allegation of bullying as submitted regardless of whether official forms are completed or if the allegation is anonymously reported.

260
00:30:13,966 --> 00:30:23,090
An allegation will be investigated as an official bullying report if the allegation is reported to a staff member and includes the below listed minimum information.

261
00:30:23,630 --> 00:30:27,632
The name and school of the target student, the name and school of the aggressors.

262
00:30:28,893 --> 00:30:40,319
The date and location of the incidents, a description of the incident that is believed to meet the criteria for bullying behavior and contact information for the reporter, which obviously required but not recommended in the event that this is.

263
00:30:42,879 --> 00:30:43,840
an anonymous report.

264
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:55,724
And then second bullet, Medford public schools will complete required bullying forms and collect missing information and signatures when a report of bullying was made that did not use approved forms.

265
00:30:55,844 --> 00:31:02,307
So what the spirit of what I tried to lay out here based on all the conversations we've had is that

266
00:31:03,519 --> 00:31:08,600
a report is like in the queue when it meets a certain amount of criteria.

267
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:17,122
And that we should, we can and should encourage parents to use the form because I think it provides guidance to like that sort of completeness.

268
00:31:17,842 --> 00:31:28,305
But that if that doesn't happen, then it is the responsibility of the school district, the investigator, whoever that is, to do the paperwork on the forms.

269
00:31:28,425 --> 00:31:32,626
So what I was trying, what I'm trying to do is be crystal clear about

270
00:31:33,606 --> 00:31:38,170
what starts the clock for parents in particular and students.

271
00:31:39,130 --> 00:31:57,484
I think we should definitely encourage the use of the form wherever we can, but also sort of recognizing like we do need consistent documentation around these things, which is why the second bullet of like whoever is doing this investigation will complete the paperwork if that hasn't already been done.

272
00:32:00,026 --> 00:32:00,306
Thoughts?

273
00:32:05,318 --> 00:32:25,788
I think in the spirit of providing clarity, one of the things when we were up, I don't know which page it was on when we were, where you gave the definition between bullying and bullying being the repeated abuse.

274
00:32:26,768 --> 00:32:30,890
And when there are other situations that are

275
00:32:31,438 --> 00:32:32,938
deemed like an incident.

276
00:32:36,379 --> 00:32:46,921
I think that our hope would be that false reports or false bullying reports are not being generated.

277
00:32:47,121 --> 00:32:58,403
But sometimes, unfortunately, when you're working with young people, young adults, sometimes people do things out of retaliation.

278
00:33:01,819 --> 00:33:10,442
we could end up with situations where false reports are coming in.

279
00:33:10,522 --> 00:33:13,863
And there have been situations where people have been accused.

280
00:33:14,723 --> 00:33:21,405
And when an investigation took place, it was found that the information was not credible.

281
00:33:22,186 --> 00:33:26,627
And so I'm just saying, as we're creating the official policy,

282
00:33:27,426 --> 00:33:34,069
that we're not opening an additional door for this to be abused.

283
00:33:35,610 --> 00:33:42,393
We do a little bit later in the document, we talk about false reporting, false allegations.

284
00:33:43,093 --> 00:33:47,275
So maybe hold that thought until we get there.

285
00:33:47,295 --> 00:33:47,876
Okay.

286
00:33:52,016 --> 00:34:14,201
Incident reporting also, we also sort of frame up that staff are required to report incidents that they witness or become aware of, that staff follow the same reporting responsibilities as students and caregivers, and that Medford will accept and investigate allegations of bullying or retaliation that are made anonymously.

287
00:34:14,261 --> 00:34:19,002
However, no disciplinary action shall be taken against a student solely on the basis of an anonymous report.

288
00:34:19,022 --> 00:34:21,783
And that's like, right, that anonymous language was right out of the law.

289
00:34:22,964 --> 00:34:24,325
Thank you, Member Graham.

290
00:34:24,425 --> 00:34:31,811
And the staff are required to formally report the incidents.

291
00:34:32,492 --> 00:34:34,633
I don't know if we want to add some kind of wording here.

292
00:34:35,854 --> 00:34:37,696
I don't know how to put it, so maybe just a note.

293
00:34:37,776 --> 00:34:46,843
But, you know, when you drive by an accident, dial 911.

294
00:34:46,883 --> 00:34:50,827
It doesn't matter if there are 20 other people there, because they're all standing around thinking somebody else dialed 911.

295
00:34:53,079 --> 00:35:05,445
And, you know, I imagine scenarios perhaps in a lunchroom where there's multiple staff members and they all see an incident happen and somebody, they each think somebody else is going to do it.

296
00:35:07,206 --> 00:35:20,593
And, you know, whether that's based on like, oh, there was an assistant principal there and I'm just a teacher or whatever, like, you know, whatever the stuff that goes on in someone's head as to like, oh, somebody else is obviously going to take care of this report.

297
00:35:21,437 --> 00:35:27,021
If there are five adults in the room who work for us, there should be five of them making sure that the report is written.

298
00:35:27,241 --> 00:35:33,665
And it doesn't matter where they are structurally in the organization, they are all responsible to make sure that one is done.

299
00:35:33,726 --> 00:35:38,449
I mean, if they go up to Mr. Tucci and said, are you going to do a report?

300
00:35:38,929 --> 00:35:39,890
And he says, yes.

301
00:35:40,833 --> 00:35:56,604
I'm not saying that we need five separate forms filled out, but short of an affirmation that somebody will be doing it and they know who it is, they are on the hook to make sure that it gets done, whether that's by them or not.

302
00:35:56,804 --> 00:36:04,649
So I just really worry about that, similar to the car accident where everybody stands around and waits for the ambulance that never got called.

303
00:36:04,669 --> 00:36:06,591
Thank you.

304
00:36:08,552 --> 00:36:08,692
Okay.

305
00:36:12,676 --> 00:36:15,660
Okay, let's move on to investigation.

306
00:36:17,573 --> 00:36:25,216
Medford Public Schools will promptly investigate all reports of bullying impacted parties and caregivers will be notified within two business days of receipt of such a report.

307
00:36:26,256 --> 00:36:27,716
We have talked about timeframes.

308
00:36:28,036 --> 00:36:32,478
I think this is what we have talked about, but open to some discussion there.

309
00:36:33,918 --> 00:36:36,159
Remain impartial through the course of any investigation.

310
00:36:36,219 --> 00:36:43,281
In the event of a conflict of interest, the investigator must disclose the conflict to their immediate supervisor within 24 hours of the receipt of the bullying report.

311
00:36:44,185 --> 00:36:50,384
Conflict of interest may include family relationships and or supervisor-supervisee relationships among other possible conflicts.

312
00:36:51,701 --> 00:37:00,484
take immediate and necessary action to ensure student safety while any investigation proceeds, and will take care to reassure those who report incidents that their involvement will remain confidential wherever possible.

313
00:37:02,044 --> 00:37:04,925
Document interviews conducted with all relevant parties.

314
00:37:05,145 --> 00:37:08,206
All notes shall become part of the record of the incident.

315
00:37:09,207 --> 00:37:19,370
Maintain a central student information system to store incident investigation forms, determinations, and disciplinary action, remediation, target safety actions taken

316
00:37:21,981 --> 00:37:24,823
alphabetically by aggressor for their graduation date.

317
00:37:25,103 --> 00:37:27,345
That came out of the last policy.

318
00:37:28,846 --> 00:37:38,472
And then discipline information also came out of the last policy, whether written or electronic as part of the temporary record will be kept for six years after the graduation of involved students.

319
00:37:38,992 --> 00:37:43,075
Temporary records must be destroyed no later than seven years after graduation of involved students.

320
00:37:43,155 --> 00:37:46,818
That came straight out of the prior policy from a record retention perspective.

321
00:37:48,558 --> 00:37:58,664
Ensure copies of all bullying investigation forms, reporting forms, if any remediation agreements and behavior plans are placed in the student file.

322
00:38:00,425 --> 00:38:05,148
This last bullet, I would like to discuss because it came out of the prior policy.

323
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:08,970
It says, and I did not update, I did not change this at all.

324
00:38:09,310 --> 00:38:17,055
Your personal notes can be kept indefinitely as long as you don't share or consult with them in the presence of parents or students.

325
00:38:17,831 --> 00:38:29,895
And that felt super alarming to me, but I didn't know if there was something I didn't know, but I wanted to specifically point that out and recommend that we strike it.

326
00:38:31,796 --> 00:38:33,697
I certainly am alarmed by it as well.

327
00:38:36,298 --> 00:38:44,060
And the days of everybody keeping a little journal that they're jotting notes in are over.

328
00:38:45,141 --> 00:38:45,861
These are going to be,

329
00:38:46,738 --> 00:39:02,603
notes that are probably largely going to be electronic and the average person, certainly the average employee's ability to maintain top-notch security on their own electronic content is not encouraging.

330
00:39:04,299 --> 00:39:08,923
Not a dig at our staff, most people are really actually quite bad at it.

331
00:39:09,043 --> 00:39:16,609
So the notion of confidential notes concerns me greatly.

332
00:39:17,310 --> 00:39:18,591
Also, what are you gonna do with them?

333
00:39:18,851 --> 00:39:21,893
Write a memoir someday about something you can't write about?

334
00:39:23,675 --> 00:39:28,779
Why you would want to keep them is also concerning.

335
00:39:28,999 --> 00:39:31,881
If it's important enough to be written down, put it in the official notes.

336
00:39:33,192 --> 00:39:47,638
I couldn't think of any legitimate reason to keep personal notes like this, but I don't work in a school, so I didn't wanna just delete it, but it felt like really, really concerning to me.

337
00:39:47,658 --> 00:39:53,301
If I may, in a different context, there are,

338
00:40:02,777 --> 00:40:09,839
some things that are kept personal that are not part of the official record or the official file.

339
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:18,181
So I am aware of that on the school side, and that's usually when we're working with legal counsel.

340
00:40:20,562 --> 00:40:23,643
And so I don't know if that's something that I,

341
00:40:24,769 --> 00:40:26,871
you know, should just get clarification on.

342
00:40:28,232 --> 00:40:30,974
Not everything is kept electronically.

343
00:40:34,117 --> 00:40:43,565
So I wasn't part of the creation of this first document, but I'm just wondering if it's related to that.

344
00:40:46,528 --> 00:40:48,450
Thank you, Dr. Robinson.

345
00:40:48,490 --> 00:40:49,451
I mean, you know,

346
00:40:50,783 --> 00:40:58,347
If there's a valid reason to be keeping your own personal notes, the word indefinitely part in particular is the part that would bother me the most.

347
00:40:58,947 --> 00:41:02,009
I mean, we have a whole thing about making sure this stuff is destroyed.

348
00:41:03,930 --> 00:41:10,653
And so even if we, if there is a valid reason that

349
00:41:11,292 --> 00:41:20,174
we find or can figure out better, which, by the way, we should include something in here to explain that, I think, for the next school committee in 10 years trying to figure out what this means.

350
00:41:21,174 --> 00:41:25,555
But indefinitely is just scary.

351
00:41:25,575 --> 00:41:34,277
I mean, our kids already, their whole lives are going to be, many of our kids' lives are going to be derailed by the digital content created

352
00:41:34,833 --> 00:41:35,633
in their teen years.

353
00:41:37,254 --> 00:41:43,637
And I just don't think we should have a policy to not making it worse or enshrining it in policy.

354
00:41:44,998 --> 00:41:47,859
So yeah, thank you.

355
00:41:47,919 --> 00:41:58,544
And we can check with Attorney Greenspan as well about whether there's some, I didn't read anything like that when I reread the law top to bottom, but I am not a lawyer.

356
00:41:58,664 --> 00:42:02,346
So I will defer to him so we can ask him that question.

357
00:42:04,478 --> 00:42:06,540
The next section is on decisions and findings.

358
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:19,433
So this is one of the references that was added from our special ed attorneys, so that we will act in accordance with Master in Law Chapter 71B, Section 3, around

359
00:42:24,537 --> 00:42:43,621
When the IEP team determines a student has a disability that affects social skills development or the student may participate in or is vulnerable to bullying, harassment, teasing because of his or her disability, the team will consider what should be included in the IEP to develop the student's skills and proficiencies to avoid and respond to bullying, harassment, or teasing.

360
00:42:43,661 --> 00:42:50,503
So that is in there to say that we know and we understand that there are potential impacts there.

361
00:42:53,410 --> 00:42:54,937
Also under decisions and findings.

362
00:42:58,001 --> 00:43:00,782
So what I did was I put two structures in here.

363
00:43:01,102 --> 00:43:06,925
One is complete the following steps if the investigator determines that bullying or retaliation has occurred.

364
00:43:08,886 --> 00:43:15,529
And so there's like notifying the police or if the principal believes there are criminal charges that may be pursued.

365
00:43:17,210 --> 00:43:21,751
Take appropriate disciplinary action consistent with the policies and procedures of Medford Public Schools.

366
00:43:21,912 --> 00:43:22,852
Notify parents.

367
00:43:26,278 --> 00:43:35,611
notify them of any action taken to prevent further acts of bullying and provide victims and aggressors with significant opportunities for counseling services.

368
00:43:36,252 --> 00:43:38,815
This can take the form, this was like right out of the prior policy.

369
00:43:40,180 --> 00:43:57,238
I then put in a structure here that says, like, if the investigator determines that bullying has not occurred, but that the incident warrants action to avoid progression of the relationship to one where bullying does occur, so this is the conflict,

370
00:43:58,055 --> 00:44:06,341
component that there are a set of steps here as well in terms of, you know, any disciplinary action, notifying parents, etc.

371
00:44:06,641 --> 00:44:10,944
So it's largely the same except for the part where we're going to notify the police in some instances.

372
00:44:13,325 --> 00:44:29,776
One thing I think we heard from parents as we have talked about this is, I think there's a belief that if bullying is not the end finding, and I think we had a related conversation about appeals last time, that that means nothing is going to happen.

373
00:44:29,976 --> 00:44:32,157
And I think that's actually not true at all.

374
00:44:32,658 --> 00:44:38,642
What if there is conflict, there still is a requirement on behalf of the district to act

375
00:44:39,422 --> 00:44:44,466
to prevent this conflict from escalating to a repeated pattern of bullying, right?

376
00:44:44,947 --> 00:44:58,639
So what I tried to do was sort of lay this out so that there were clear responsibilities of the district, whether bullying has occurred by the determination of the investigator or whether conflict has occurred.

377
00:44:58,819 --> 00:45:01,381
And so that's the structure here that I tried to set up.

378
00:45:03,719 --> 00:45:10,000
And then act to create a stable environment for victims and aggressors, regardless of whether bullying or conflict has occurred.

379
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:15,981
Interventions may include, this table was in the prior policy.

380
00:45:16,001 --> 00:45:25,523
I think it's helpful for people to understand that these things could be the kinds of things that happen in both cases, bullying or conflict.

381
00:45:27,424 --> 00:45:32,525
And then there's a bullet here that, you know, when we're talking about findings,

382
00:45:35,048 --> 00:45:44,134
Discipline any student who knowingly makes a false accusation of bullying or retaliation per the approved disciplinary policies of Medford Public Schools.

383
00:45:44,775 --> 00:45:52,620
If the false allegations have civil and or criminal elements, further actions may be referred to by the appropriate law enforcement agency.

384
00:45:55,622 --> 00:45:58,804
This set of references and links

385
00:46:02,449 --> 00:46:10,396
is was provided by our special ed attorneys, I think we also have some links to our policies that will need to be added in here.

386
00:46:10,416 --> 00:46:13,539
And.

387
00:46:17,062 --> 00:46:18,323
We probably we probably.

